episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror XI
episodes.plot: Homer must do one good deed to get into Heaven; Bart and Lisa encounter a witch in a gingerbread house; Super-intelligent dolphins strike back at humanity.

episodes.title: A Tale of Two Springfields
episodes.plot: Springfield is split in two when Homer revolts because his area code is changed; the new town walls itself off from the neighbors.

episodes.title: Insane Clown Poppy
episodes.plot: After he learns he has a daughter, Krusty turns to Homer for parenting advice.

episodes.title: Lisa the Treehugger
episodes.plot: Lisa's crush on an environmental activist inspires her to live in a tree threatened by loggers.

episodes.title: Homer vs. Dignity
episodes.plot: Desperate for money, Homer accepts payment from Mr. Burns in exchange for humiliating himself.

episodes.title: The Computer Wore Menace Shoes
episodes.plot: Homer's gossip website becomes a huge hit, but when his information runs out he resorts to making up news.

episodes.title: The Great Money Caper
episodes.plot: The whole town of Springfield conspires to teach Homer and Bart a lesson after the pair begin running confidence scams.

episodes.title: Skinner's Sense of Snow
episodes.plot: A freak blizzard traps the students of Springfield Elementary inside their school. Their lives at stake, they are at the mercy of the rescue efforts of a woozy Homer and Ned.

episodes.title: HOMR
episodes.plot: An X-ray reveals a crayon lodged in Homer's brain. After the crayon is removed, Homer experiences a sudden surge in intelligence, making him closer to Lisa and isolated from his friends.

episodes.title: Pokey Mom
episodes.plot: Marge befriends a convict with an artistic streak. Meanwhile, Homer battles the chiropractic industry after he creates a miracle back pain cure.

episodes.title: Worst Episode Ever
episodes.plot: Bart and Milhouse are left in charge of the comic book store after Comic Book Guy is hospitalized.

episodes.title: Tennis the Menace
episodes.plot: Homer installs a tennis court in the backyard, but his lousy playing creates a rift in the family.

episodes.title: Day of the Jackanapes
episodes.plot: When a new television game show grows in popularity and begins to draw away Krusty's TV audience e decided to retire from the television business.

episodes.title: New Kids on the Blecch
episodes.plot: A music producer offers Bart and his friends a chance to participate in an up-and-coming boyband, but the boys are not up to it after making a discovery.

episodes.title: Hungry Hungry Homer
episodes.plot: Homer is forced to go on a hunger strike by the Springfield Isotopes after uncovering a secret plan to have the baseball team moved to New Mexico.

episodes.title: Bye Bye Nerdy
episodes.plot: Problems with a bully lead Lisa to examine just what makes bullies aggressive. Meanwhile, Homer gets into the baby-proofing business.

episodes.title: Simpson Safari
episodes.plot: The Simpsons win a trip to Africa after Homer finds a golden animal cracker from the 60's in the loft.

episodes.title: Trilogy of Error
episodes.plot: Homer's rush to the hospital to re-attach his severed thumb, Lisa's rush to school to win the science fair, and Bart's run-in with an illegal fireworks scheme interconnect from their point of view.

episodes.title: I'm Goin' to Praiseland
episodes.plot: With Homer's help, Flanders tries to establish a Christian theme park based on drawings in Maude's sketch book.

episodes.title: Children of a Lesser Clod
episodes.plot: After a debilitating injury forces him to stay indoors, Homer begins a daycare center.

episodes.title: Simpsons Tall Tales
episodes.plot: A hobo tells the Simpsons tall tales on a train ride to Delaware. In the first story, Homer is outcast from society as Paul Bunyan. Then, Lisa travels the country planting trees as Connie Appleseed. Finally, Bart and Nelson raft down the Mississippi as Tom Sawyer and Huck Finn.
